        "notes": "",
        "sessionLog": "Session 3 — Murder at Ismeri Library<br><br>The party chose not to return the <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"item\" data-mention-id=\"JXAj1bY05R1LfpKG\" data-mention-uuid=\"Item.JXAj1bY05R1LfpKG\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Orzhov Crystal</span>&nbsp;to <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"actor\" data-mention-id=\"KtUG0Wlb74NQH5B7\" data-mention-uuid=\"Actor.KtUG0Wlb74NQH5B7\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Sable, Dimir Informant</span>&nbsp;.<br><br>Instead, they arranged a meeting with Vethis inside the <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"scene\" data-mention-id=\"bhlZHSWETMa9p1LT\" data-mention-uuid=\"Scene.bhlZHSWETMa9p1LT\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Ismeri Library</span>&nbsp;.<br><br>Bringing <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"actor\" data-mention-id=\"TVmFW8umyCeSrLNd\" data-mention-uuid=\"Actor.TVmFW8umyCeSrLNd\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Guttersnipe</span>&nbsp;along proved catastrophic.<br><br>He improvised an explosive device.<br><br>The bomb killed <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"item\" data-mention-id=\"lMNhvQ8C8O51raJz\" data-mention-uuid=\"Item.lMNhvQ8C8O51raJz\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Vethis Ledger</span>&nbsp;.<br><br>The party escaped before authorities arrived and regrouped at the <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"scene\" data-mention-id=\"EP5IdhprUDApVniM\" data-mention-uuid=\"Scene.EP5IdhprUDApVniM\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Merl Inn</span>&nbsp;in <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"journal\" data-mention-id=\"I4CMlZUAE46BppMb\" data-mention-uuid=\"JournalEntry.I4CMlZUAE46BppMb\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Precinct Five</span>.<br><br>Later, a mysterious Merfolk investigator approached them, asking for help understanding the escaped Simic monsters.<br><br>The party ignored the request.",
