      {
        "id": "taKFO7UydkKrMEyT",
        "title": "",
        "sessionNumber": 8,
        "status": "completed",
        "inGameDate": "",
        "realDate": "",
        "notes": "",
        "sessionLog": "Sessio 8 - A cursed place to call home<br><br>The party started in the <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"scene\" data-mention-id=\"Pjyr57b4ojE89HEy\" data-mention-uuid=\"Scene.Pjyr57b4ojE89HEy\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Moon Market</span>&nbsp; after two weeks of downtime following the branding/disgrace fallout.<br>They browsed several black-market vendors and bought or negotiated for gear, potions, and odd items, including a love potion, climbing potion, illusion-related items, and a key piece for a future crafted device.<br>They learned there are three components needed to build a ghost-busting/resonance-disrupting weapon: a <strong>resonance crystal, a capacitor,</strong> and a <strong>harmonic focusing lens.</strong><br>The group first traveled to the haunted house in the Moon Market area, where they met <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"actor\" data-mention-id=\"U3vuPhhpBjQUlDXn\" data-mention-uuid=\"Actor.U3vuPhhpBjQUlDXn\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Professor Mizzix</span>&nbsp;, a renowned goblin scholar studying resonance anomalies.<br>Mizzix explained that the house is haunted by ghosts interfering with his work and asked the party to help him gather the three components so he can build the device.<br>The party then traveled to the <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"scene\" data-mention-id=\"ahs7O0rdHVyZDHBB\" data-mention-uuid=\"Scene.ahs7O0rdHVyZDHBB\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Red Waste Cave</span>&nbsp; and recovered the resonance crystal from a ritual/cave-like site inhabited by ractose performers.<br>They then headed to the <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"scene\" data-mention-id=\"QnGZaORg2lozuqXb\" data-mention-uuid=\"Scene.QnGZaORg2lozuqXb\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Azorius Vault</span>&nbsp;and used social tricks and roleplay to get access.<br><span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"actor\" data-mention-id=\"7lfMDP0Pvx6u7gx7\" data-mention-uuid=\"Actor.7lfMDP0Pvx6u7gx7\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Frikka The Fuse</span>&nbsp;successfully retrieved the harmonic focusing lens from inside the vault by slipping past the warded area and opening a contraption with Tinker’s tools.<br>Back at Mizzix’s lab, the party brought him the crystal, lens, and capacitor, and together they assembled a powerful laser-pistol-style ghostbuster weapon.<br>They returned to the haunted house and fought a wraith/ghostly Azorius bureaucrat that had been haunting the place.<br>The fight ended with the ghost being destroyed and the house becoming their new <span class=\"nd-mention\" data-nd-mention=\"\" data-mention-kind=\"scene\" data-mention-id=\"13JAHX28BeSlp79g\" data-mention-uuid=\"Scene.13JAHX28BeSlp79g\" contenteditable=\"false\">@Bastion</span>&nbsp;/home base.<br>They also earned a charisma-boosting meditation room, some gold, and a recommendation letter, and were told they can stash loot there safely and potentially improve the house later.<br>The session ended with the party settling into their new base and discussing future plans, including dealing with their brands and other open quests.<br>Main outcomes:<br><br>New bastion/home acquired<br>Ghost defeated<br>Ghostbuster weapon created<br>Key quest items recovered",
        "createdDate": "2026-07-19T03:06:15.591Z",
        "source": "live",
